Colleagues,

 

we would like to invite you in the name of the Secure Unified Endpoint Management Productline to our Area Review.

It's purpose is to share results of new features for the most recent iterations delivered by the Secure Unified Endpoint Management teams. 

 

Meeting is not mandatory, but your PARTICIPATION and FEEDBACK will be HIGHLY APPRECIATED.

 

Agenda will be provided at the beginning of the meeting. The topics are related to Empirum, EgoSecure EDP, Silverback and  UUX.

This meeting occurs every two weeks.

Recorded Sessions can be found in our R&D Yammer Channel "R&D News <https://www.yammer.com/support.matrix42.com/#/threads/inGroup?type=in_group&feedId=19326763008&view=all> " 

 

Thank you and we are looking forward to see you soon!

 

Regards,

Your SUEM Team

Subject: DWP (CLPLF) Area Review
Optional Attendees: M42_Technik;Madelyn Henzler-Hernandez;Fabian Henzler;Britta Bujard;Sven Torsten Scherz;Anna Juergens;Andrey Voronov;M42 R&D Germany;M42 R&D Ukraine;M42 R&D Belarus;M42_Support;M42 PreSales;M42_PSO;Marketing;Channel;Product Strategy;Dirk Eisenberg;Marius-Cristian Stefan;Markus Schaefer;Yuliia Hyl;Mircea-Ionel Strutu;George-Sorin Ivascu;Horia-Valentin Simon;Beni Godoi;Iulian-Andrei Popescu;Andrei-Ioan Bublea;Larisa-Mihaela Blejan;Tania-Maria Rosca;Teodor-Lucian Stoica
Description:
Hi everybody,




Rescheduling our Area Review to include our US colleagues, so they can also attend.

 


So, in the name of the “Cloud & Platform” (DWP) Productline, we want to invite you to a “Productline Review” that will take place every 2 weeks.

 

Purpose of this session, will be, that you’ll get informed about changes that have been implemented during this period of time and get some insights about relevant decisions made by the Productline “Cloud & Platform”.

 

As mentioned this meeting will happen on a regular basis, every 2 weeks and will take roughly 1 hour. According to the fact that we’ve re-organized the Productlines, it can also be possible that we need to adjust the timeslot in future.

 

Of course this session will also be a possibility for you to contribute to the Productline with your feedback.

 

Also if you are not able to join this meeting “live”, we will record this session for you.

 

So we would be very happy to welcome you to the “Productline Review”. We are looking forward seeing you there…!

 

Regards,

Your Cloud & Platform Team

Optional Attendees: M42_Technik;Madelyn Henzler-Hernandez;Fabian Henzler;Britta Bujard;Sven Torsten Scherz;Anna Juergens;Andrey Voronov;M42 R&D Germany;M42 R&D Ukraine;M42 R&D Belarus;M42_Support;M42 PreSales;M42_PSO;Marketing;Channel;Product Strategy;Dirk Eisenberg;Marius-Cristian Stefan;Markus Schaefer;Yuliia Hyl;Mircea-Ionel Strutu;George-Sorin Ivascu;Horia-Valentin Simon;Beni Godoi;Iulian-Andrei Popescu;Andrei-Ioan Bublea;Larisa-Mihaela Blejan;Tania-Maria Rosca;Teodor-Lucian Stoica
Description:
Hi everybody,




Rescheduling our Area Review to include our US colleagues, so they can also attend.

 


So, in the name of the “Cloud & Platform” (DWP) Productline, we want to invite you to a “Productline Review” that will take place every 2 weeks.

 

Purpose of this session, will be, that you’ll get informed about changes that have been implemented during this period of time and get some insights about relevant decisions made by the Productline “Cloud & Platform”.

 

As mentioned this meeting will happen on a regular basis, every 2 weeks and will take roughly 1 hour. According to the fact that we’ve re-organized the Productlines, it can also be possible that we need to adjust the timeslot in future.

 

Of course this session will also be a possibility for you to contribute to the Productline with your feedback.

 

Also if you are not able to join this meeting “live”, we will record this session for you.

 

So we would be very happy to welcome you to the “Productline Review”. We are looking forward seeing you there…!

 

Regards,

Your Cloud & Platform Team

Description:
Dear Matricians, 

 

Let’s take a break together!

 

Our weekly online courses will help you move, activate, and mobilize your body with exercises for your back and neck. 
Exercises to improve your coordination and balance are also included!

 

Get into comfortable clothes and grab a sport mat for a better experience.

 

Don’t hesitate to turn on your cameras to create a lively atmosphere.

 

Best regards, 

Your People & Culture Team

Team,

Tom

Description:
Hi all,

 

in the name of the ESM Productline, I want to invite you to the “ESM Area Review” that will take place every 4 weeks.

 

Purpose of this session, will be, that you’ll get informed about changes that have been implemented during this period of time and get some insights about relevant decisions made by the ESM Productline.

 

As mentioned this meeting will happen on a regular basis, every 4 weeks and will take roughly 1 hour. 

 

Of course this session will also be a possibility for you to contribute to the Productline with your feedback.

 

Also if you are not able to join this meeting “live”, we will record this session for you.

 

So we would be very happy to welcome you to the “ESM Area Review”. We are looking forward seeing you there…!

 

Regards,

Your ESM Team

Subject: Quarterly Strategy Update - OKR Coaching (3/4)
Description:
Team

 

I am going to run a coaching session on objectives & key results (OKRs) for product teams.  Given we intend to transition our planning approach to OKRs for Q2 I wanted to insert this session to help enable you to help us make the transition as we start planning for next quarter.

 

I have included everyone on the invite, as I think it will be a beneficial session for everyone to understand how we will work with OKRs and not just those leading the planning process.  I would therefore encourage everyone to attend, but will also run a duplicate session in the near future.

 

Mike

Subject: Quarterly Strategy Update - Kick-off (1/4)
Optional Attendees: Taras Chopko;Kateryna Babchenko;Marius-Cristian Stefan;Klaus Ziegerhofer;Yevheniia Hrakhovska;Horia Simon;Enrico Nicolai;Serhii Kryvinskyi;Tetiana Kanaieva;Klaus Schaeffer;Valentyn Buriak;Markus Schaefer;George Mandresi;Tania Rosca;Miralem Cebic;Sebastian Sziegel;Oleh Shyshka;Silke Henderson-Stuenkel;Jan Giese;Alexandru Ioana;Florian Heinrich;Michael Ascher;Christian Hasselbach;Enis Sameric;Vasyl Zhushma;Dylan Harris (External);Viktor Suvorov;Serhii Deneha;Soenke Dirksen;Beni Godoi (External);Mircea Strutu;Madelyn Henzler-Hernandez;Serhii Ivanov;Gero Diehsner;Horst Droege;Ruediger Winter;Sven Torsten Scherz;Iulian Popescu;Andrei Dutu;Jannik Hesse;Mykhailo Horelov;Joachim Knoth;Sorin Ivascu;Larisa Blejan;Torsten Boch;Denys Abrashyn;Anastasiia Zhytnyk;Herve Burtin (External);Yevhenii Maksymenko;Paul Usurelu;Yurii Lipatov;Matthias Vogt;Daniel Stanciu;David Vollmers;Varvara Groza;Mykola Grachov;Oleksii Bolkhovskyi;Antonela Negulescu;Dmytro Taldykin;Vitalii Kozlovskyi;Peter Kress;Maik Fuhr;Jens Beimel;Svitlana Komisar;Dirk Eisenberg;Andrei Bublea;Oleksandr Statnikov;Karl Tews;Vadym Zinoviev;Catalin Marcadonatu;Mihai Usurelu;Gaurav Raghava;Alina Pereverzieva;Tiberiu Petre;Carsten Franke;Volodymyr Shevchenko;Lucian Welter;Joerg Kroner;Andrii Tymchenko;Christian Wolf;Yuliia Borodatova;Philipp Bessler;Vivien Elvy Kim;Teodor Stoica;Mykola Hryshchuk;Mykola Melnyk;Harald Neubert
Description:
Team

 

I wanted to invite everyone to the first part of the planning kick-off for next quarter.  The objectives of this session are:

 

1.	Communicate the planned new product organisation formation and show how it aligns with the transformation principles shared with you in earlier sessions.
2.	Show how the planned new formation aligns with our product strategy and sets us up for future success and accelerated growth.
3.	Discuss how we will gear up for the new quarter differently including making the transition from planning using feature-based product roadmaps to using product OKRs.

 

We will not need the full 90 minutes and there will be lots of opportunity for questions.

 

Mike

Subject: Einladung zur Wahl der Schwerbehindertenvertretung
Description:
Liebe Kolleginnen und Kollegen,

nach § 177 Abs. 1 SGB IX werden in Betrieben, in denen wenigstens fünf schwerbehinderte Menschen bzw. gleichgestellte behinderte Menschen nicht nur vorübergehend beschäftigt sind, eine Vertrauensperson der schwerbehinderten Menschen und wenigstens ein/e Stellvertreter/in gewählt.

Diese Voraussetzung ist in unserem Betrieb erfüllt. Derzeit ist in unserem Betrieb jedoch keine Schwerbehindertenvertretung vorhanden.

Die Wahl der Schwerbehindertenvertretung findet gemäß § 18 Wahlordnung Schwerbehindertenvertretungen (SchwbVWO) im vereinfachten Wahlverfahren statt.

Somit laden wir euch zur Wahlversammlung am 02.03.2023 um 15:30 Uhr in den Meetingraum Endeavor ein.

In dieser Versammlung sollen eine Person als Schwerbehindertenvertretung und deren Stellvertreter gewählt werden. Wahlberechtigt sind gemäß § 1 Abs. 2 Satz 1 SchwbVWO alle in unserem Betrieb beschäftigten schwerbehinderten Menschen und ihnen Gleichgestellte.

Wählbar sind alle Arbeitnehmer, die mindestens 6 Monate und nicht nur vorübergehend im Betrieb beschäftigt sind und das 18. Lebensjahr vollendet haben.

Wichtiger Hinweis: Bitte bringt zum Nachweis der Wahlberechtigung vorhandene Nachweise über eure Eigenschaft als schwerbehinderter oder gleichgestellter Mensch mit. Es wird dem Arbeitgeber gegenüber nicht mitgeteilt, wer an der Versammlung teilnimmt.

 

Geplanter Ablauf:

1.	Die Wahlberechtigten bestimmen mit einfacher Mehrheit eine Person als Wahlleitung.
2.	Nach Sammlung der Kandidaturvorschläge wird mit einfacher Mehrheit die Anzahl der Stellvertreter bestimmt.
3.	Wahl der Schwerbehindertenvertretung mittels geheimer Wahl
4.	Wahl der Stellvertreter (1 Wahlgang) mittels geheimer Wahl

Nach § 178 Abs. 6 SGB IX hat die Versäumnis von Arbeitszeit im Zusammenhang mit der Teilnahme an der Wahlversammlung keine Minderung des Arbeitsentgelts zur Folge.

Viele Grüße,

Euer Betriebsrat
